---

## 5. Risk Analysis

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|-----------|
| Limited access to WSM data | Model parameters cannot be fully calibrated | Use scenario-based estimates or anonymized aggregated data |
| Incomplete maintenance history | Uncertain failure distributions | Apply statistical estimation and sensitivity analysis |
| Model complexity becomes too high | Delays in implementation | Simplify model scope and focus on key parameters |
| Confidentiality restrictions | Certain values cannot be published | Present results in normalized or indexed form |
| Time constraints during modelling phase | Reduced analysis depth | Prioritize core model functionality first |

---

## 6. Expected Outcome of Phase 2

At the end of Phase 2, the project will have:

- A clearly defined model structure
- A documented research methodology
- Identified data sources and required parameters
- A project schedule for the remaining thesis work
- A risk management plan

This planning phase establishes the foundation required to proceed to **Phase 3**, where data collection, model implementation, and simulation analysis will be conducted.
